        <updateDate>2017-11-20T16:33:50Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Preventing Tragedies Between Police and Communities Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill requires a state or local government that receives funding under the Edward Byrne Memorial Justice Assistance Grant (JAG) program to train law enforcement officers on de-escalation techniques. The Department of Justice (DOJ) may reduce by up to 20% the JAG allocation of a state or local government that fails to comply.</p> <p>DOJ must collect data on the efforts of state and local governments to enhance de-escalation training for law enforcement officers.</p> <p>Additionally, a state or local government that receives JAG program funding must enact a law, policy, or procedure that establishes an affirmative duty on a law enforcement officer to use de-escalation techniques. DOJ must reduce by 15% the JAG allocation of a state or local government that fails to enact such law, policy, or procedure.</p> <p> DOJ must issue guidance on compliance with these requirements.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
